div.p:
The first step was to search for annotated texts with corresponding French translations. Using the "Dialogism Novel" project (Vishnubhotla et al., 2022; (https://www.adamhammond.com /pdnc/), which includes annotations for 28 English novels, we sought corresponding French translations online. The list is available in Annex 1. Only one of them has yet to be translated and made available in French; 17 of them are translated and copyright-free and available on the web (for the most important part on 

                            www.wikidata.org
                        ), in gray in Annex 1. Our experiments so far have been conducted on 9 of the 17 available novels. See Annex 1 for details.
